<br>
Total Mana Pool = Level x ((INT/5) +2) + EquipmentMana<br>
<br>
Using this, I calculated the following to try and help clear up the confusion about how much INT will be required by different level players to obtain the mana required to cast Mass Mystical Transvergence.  I can't garantee the above forumla is accurate, but it's as good a starting place as any.<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> 
Required INT by level to cast Mass Mystical Transvergence:

Level 56 Magician needs 236 INT to reach 2750 mana pool.
Level 57 Magician needs 232 INT to reach 2750 mana pool.
Level 58 Magician needs 228 INT to reach 2750 mana pool.
Level 59 Magician needs 224 INT to reach 2750 mana pool.
Level 60 Magician needs 220 INT to reach 2750 mana pool.</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> 
Required INT by Race at level 56 (assuming you put 25 points into INT):

Human     has 110 INT so at level 56 requires 126 INT from gear and buffs.
High Elf  has 127 INT so at level 56 requires 109 INT from gear and buffs.
Gnome     has 133 INT so at level 56 requires 103 INT from gear and buffs.
Dark Elf  has 134 INT so at level 56 requires 102 INT from gear and buffs.
Erudite   has 142 INT so at level 56 requires  94 INT from gear and buffs.</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END-->I hope that helps. <p><FONT SIZE="3" COLOR=#FFFFFF FACE="Comic Sans MS, Sans-Serif, Courier New, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">
