<br>
Up to 200: One point of INT is 12 mana.<br>
After 200: One point of INT is 6 mana.<br>
<br>
At 50, one point of INT pre-201 is 10 mana.  At 55, it becomes 11.  So at 56 it's 11.2 mana per INT pre-201.<br>
<br>
Assuming I'm right anyhoo, which I may not be. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=izudin>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#333333>(10/19/02 9:02:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1035.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Thanks so far</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the replies so far. I must admit I have never in all my career really cared about equipment (took what I could get when I had a chance) but now I get the bill for it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Then again this never really hurt me in all my lvls...<br>
